medical_history.chief_complaint: Acute onset nausea, vomiting, and abdominal pain.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: Symptoms began today at around 16:30 with constant abdominal pain radiating to the back and epigastric area. The patient experienced two episodes of whitish-yellow vomiting. There were no fevers, chills, or gastrointestinal symptoms prior to the onset.
medical_history.past_medical_history: Prostate adenocarcinoma status post radiation therapy, diabetes mellitus type II, end-stage renal disease status post living unrelated renal transplant, hypertension, hyperlipidemia, Parkinsonism, appendectomy, latent tuberculosis status post isoniazid treatment, obstructive sleep apnea not on CPAP, hypothyroidism following treatment for toxic multinodular goiter, and squamous cell carcinoma.
